<div id="mn"> <h2> neuroscience in the news </h2>

<img src="gif/neuronewsp.jpg" width="230" height="188" alt="newspaper brain"
class="flr" />

<p> What&#39;s going on in the world of neuroscience?  What&#39;s new?  
What's happening?  With fascinating stories that focus on brain research, 
this page will keep you informed about the breaking discoveries and events 
in neuroscience.</p>

<ul>

<li><a href="<www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2024/03/240307110756.htm"> 
Doctors can now watch spinal cord activity during surgery</a>, 
University of California - Riverside, ScienceDaily, March 7, 2024.
</li>

<li><a 
href="http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2024/03/240308123326.htm"> 
Small class sizes not better for pupils' grades or resilience, says 
study</a>, Taylor & Francis Group, ScienceDaily, March 8, 2024. </li>

<li><a 
href="http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2024/03/240308122958.htm"> 
Lack of focus doesn't equal lack of intelligence -- it's proof of an 
intricate brain</a>, ScienceDaily, March 8, 2024. </li>

<li><a 
href="http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2024/03/240310194811.htm"> 
Blood-based marker developed to identify sleep deprivation</a>, 
University of Birmingham, ScienceDaily, March 10, 2024. </li>

<li><a 
href="http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2024/03/240311145901.htm"> 
Researchers uncover protein responsible for cold sensation</a>, 
University of Michigan, ScienceDaily, March 11, 2024. </li>

<li><a 
href="http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2024/03/240311145758.htm"> 
Wrist device that monitors activity could help provide early warning of 
Alzheimer's</a>, Johns Hopkins Bloomberg School of Public Health 
ScienceDaily, March 11, 2024. </li>

<li><a 
href="http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2024/03/240311145739.htm"> 
Shared blueprint in brain development across different functional 
areas</a>, University of Minnesota Medical School, ScienceDaily, March 
11, 2024. </li>

<li><a 
href="http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2024/03/240312133923.htm"> 
Researchers identify distinct sleep types and their impact on long-term 
health</a>, Penn State, ScienceDaily, March 12, 2024. </li>

<li><a href="www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2024/03/240313135340.htm"> 
First recognition of self in the mirror is spurred by touch</a>, 
University of Texas at Austin, ScienceDaily, March 13, 2024. </li>

<li><a 
href="https://www.nih.gov/news-events/news-releases/nih-researchers-identify-brain-connections-associated-adhd-youth">NIH 
researchers identify brain connections associated with ADHD in 
youth</a>, NIH News Releases, March 13, 2024.</li>

<li><a 
href="http://https://directorsblog.nih.gov/2024/03/14/study-suggests-during-sleep-neural-process-helps-clear-the-brain-of-damaging-waste/">Study 
Suggests During Sleep, Neural Process Helps Clear the Brain of Damaging 
Waste</a>, NIH Director's Blog, March 14, 2024.</li>

<li><a 
href="http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2024/03/240325114155.htm"> 
Greener streets linked to better sleep</a>, University of Exeter, 
ScienceDaily, March 25, 2024. </li>

<li><a 
href="http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2024/03/240320122455.htm"> 
New archive of ancient human brains challenges misconceptions of soft 
tissue preservation</a>, University of Oxford ScienceDaily, March 25, 
2024. </li>

<li><a 
href="http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2024/03/240327124753.htm"> 
Getting too little sleep linked to high blood pressure</a>, American 
College of Cardiology, ScienceDaily, March 27, 2024. </li>

<li><a 
href="http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2024/03/240327124725.htm"> 
Want to feel young? Protect your sleep</a>, Stockholm University, 
ScienceDaily, March 27, 2024. </li>

<li><a 
href="http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2024/04/240401142451.htm"> 
App may pave way to treatments for no. 1 dementia in under-60s</a>, 
University of California - San Francisco, ScienceDaily, April 1, 2024. 
</li>

<li><a 
href="http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2024/04/240401142454.htm"> 
Universal brain-computer interface lets people play games with just 
their thoughts</a>, University of Texas at Austin, ScienceDaily, April 
1, 2024. </li>

<li><a 
href="https://www.nih.gov/news-events/news-releases/irregular-sleep-late-bedtimes-associated-worse-grades-high-school-students">Irregular 
sleep and late bedtimes associated with worse grades for high school 
students</a>, NIH News Release, April 2, 2024.</li>

<li><a 
href="https://www.nih.gov/news-events/nih-research-matters/skin-test-detects-evidence-parkinson-s-related-disorders">Skin 
test detects evidence of Parkinson’s and related disorders</a>, NIH 
Research Matters, April 2, 2024.</li>

<li><a 
href="http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2024/04/240404190712.htm"> 
Prairie voles display signs of human-like depression</a>, University of 
Texas at El Paso, ScienceDaily, April 4, 2024. </li>

<li><a 
href="http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2024/04/240405130449.htm"> 
The sense of smell is influenced by cues from other senses</a>, 
Stockholm University, ScienceDaily, April 5, 2024. </li>

<li><a 
href="http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2024/04/240408130746.htm">A 
friendly pat on the back can improve performance in basketball</a>, 
University of Basel, ScienceDaily, April 8, 2024. </li>

<li><a 
href="http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2024/04/240408130630.htm"> 
Disparities in sleep health and insomnia may begin at a young age</a>, 
Penn State, ScienceDaily, April 8, 2024. </li>

<li><a 
href="http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2024/04/240410112638.htm"> 
Brain stimulation treatment may improve depression, anxiety in older 
adults</a>, University of Florida, ScienceDaily, April 10, 2024. </li>

<li><a 
href="https://directorsblog.nih.gov/2024/04/25/study-suggests-treatments-that-unleash-immune-cells-in-the-brain-could-help-combat-alzheimers/">study 
suggests treatments that unleash immune cells in the brain could help 
combat Alzheimer’s, NIH Director's Blog, April 25, 2024.</li>

<li><a 
href="https://www.nih.gov/news-events/news-releases/scientists-discover-how-essential-nutrient-enters-brain">Scientists 
discover how an essential nutrient enters the brain</a>, NIH News 
Release, May 1, 2024.</li>

</ul>

